investigators on thursday focused on 
the charge that propelled an errant rocket into a crowd watching 
the towns july fourth fireworks display injuring 18 people 
the sixinch rocket went off course skidded hundreds of feet 
and showered the tightly packed gathering of about 10000 people 
with burning debris after the rack that held it tipped over 
wednesday night authorities said 
it was like a cannon shot into the crowd fire chief bernard 
lach said there was a big white flash and then a lot of 
commotion 
four people including a 3yearold boy were hospitalized with 
burns all were listed thursday in stable condition the others 
suffered minor injuries and were treated at a hospital and 
released 
all i can gather is the rack blew up and tipped over on its 
side said ken lupoli who set up the fireworks display 
