come saturday the moon will be full and 
so will ted walkers farm 
hundreds of pickers fiddlers and crooners will gather on 
walkers rural spread near nashville to pay tribute to luna from 
nightfall to sunrise at another full moon bluegrass party a 
13yearold tradition 
the parties have attracted crowds of 1000 to 1500 people and 
have seen wellknown musicians such as chet atkins and wynonna judd 
sitting in with carpenters accountants and housewives for 
impromptu jam sessions 
the full moon just brings out something special in people 
walker said theyre up tempo and the moon is up tempo and 
everything is full energy 
