universitys publications department 
instruments range from banjos and guitars to spoons and 
washboards the singing ranges from great to terrible says walker 
a nashville lawyer when hes not throwing bluegrass parties 
im a terrible singer but they put up with me because its 
my party he said 
the full moon parties started in august 1977 when walker and 
some friends decided to have a jam session in the country where 
the moonlight is brighter than in the city they picked his 
homestead in williamson county about 20 miles southwest of 
nashville 
they enjoyed themselves so much they did it again the next full 
moon and the tradition was on 
fiddlers and frolickers used to gather at nightfall any day the 
full moon rose from april to october 
this year the parties will be held only on warm weekend nights 
that coincide with the full moon 
i guess im getting old said walker 48 
but partyers will continue to jam through the night every 
full moon is followed by a day off he said 
the gatherings have gotten so big that walker hires a parking 
crew and a cleanup crew and keeps everyone in touch with beepers 
and cellular phones 
walker realized in 1980 that the partys size had truly gotten 
out of hand a rowdy stranger told him to go home and not come 
back 
