<TEXT>
almost every week since midmay bombs 
blamed on leftists have rocked the greek capital but while terror 
groups have been wiped out elsewhere in europe greece has failed 
to arrest a single suspect 
most of the bombings in greece are believed to be the work of a 
shadowy group called november 17 or of other groups inspired by 
them 
november 17 which takes its name from the day in 1973 when the 
rightwing military junta crushed a student rebellion first 
surfaced in december 1975 with the assassination of athens cia 
station chief richard welch 
the united states has called november 17 one of the deadliest 
terrorist groups in europe in the past 14 years the group has 
assassinated 14 people including three us officials 
despite promises to crack down on terrorism successive greek 
governments both conservative and socialist have failed to 
arrest a single homegrown terrorist 
experts say november 17s success in evading arrest depends 
mainly on their own ruthless efficiency small membership and a 
police force that appears to have been unprepared to deal with 
urban terrorism 
premier constantine mitsotakis whose conservative new democracy 
party won a slender victory in aprils election has a personal 
reason to want to do better than his predecessors in stamping out 
terrorism last year november 17 assassinated his soninlaw 
pavlos bakoyannis 
