boris n yeltsin warned communist party 
traditionalists friday that the price of their intransigence will 
be nationalization of party property and demands that they stand 
trial for ruining soviet society 
yeltsin brought the wave of public indignation that propelled 
him to the presidency of the huge russian republic to the fifth day 
of the 28th communist party congress at the kremlins palace of 
congresses 
reformers got their chance to fight back against the communist 
traditionalists who dominated the first week of the congress and 
blamed mikhail s gorbachev for the partys loss of popularity and 
ideological drift 
it is an illusion to think that after all dissenters all who 
do not wish to be drive belts and cogs of the apparatus quit the 
party it will retain all the property of the soviet communist 
party and the associated authority he said 
it will not be so if this is the case the people will 
start struggling for the full nationalization of the property of 
the party yeltsin said the party will be bankrupt obliged to 
repay its debts to the people if only with its property 
an effort might be made to prosecute party leaders at every 
level for the damage they personally have inflicted on the party 
and the people he said 
yeltsins warning was a prediction of a day of reckoning for the 
communist party which nationalized property and violently 
repressed its enemies when it seized power under lenin in 1917 
