be the work of rightwing extremists authorities said 
the bombing was the most serious of six explosions in the past 
week in johannesburg white extremists claimed responsibility for 
the previous blasts but there was no such claim following fridays 
explosion 
the ultraright and neofascist forces are on the 
rampage said the african national congress the countrys 
largest black opposition group the anc demands that authorities 
disarm and disband the ultraright groups 
the bomb went off in the city center during the morning rush 
hour in an area where buses used by blacks let off and pick up 
passengers thousands of blacks from townships outside johannesburg 
pass through the area every day 
police said the bomb hidden in a trash can sent pieces of 
concrete and debris hurtling through the air hitting people 
standing in bus lines and passersby 
doctors said most of the injuries were relatively minor and just 
two of the 27 blacks treated at a local hospital were required to 
stay for additional treatment 
police said the blast looked like the work of rightwing white 
extremists no arrests have been made 
three black minibuses were were riddled with debris and about 
15 other vehicles suffered lesser damage witnesses said 
we just heard a big noise everyone scattered people in the 
taxis got out and ran away said nhlandla mbatha who was waiting 
in a bus line when the bomb went off there were rocks flying 
into the air there was blood everywhere people were screaming 
and crying 
some of the injured were buying food in nearby shops when they 
were hit by flying debris witnesses said 
everything was clouded with smoke i saw about six people 
running toward me with shredded clothing and some with no shoes 
said shopkeeper isha charassi 
police cars and ambulances with wailing sirens rushed to the 
scene of the blast the most serious since the bombing campaign 
began a week ago 
rightwing whites have expressed outrage at president fw de 
klerks stated plans to end apartheid and share power with the 
countrys 30 million blacks at present the 5 million whites 
dominate politics and the economy 
the previous bombs were aimed at whites involved in efforts to 
end apartheid but caused no injuries and only minor damage a 
shadowy group calling itself the white wolves claimed 
responsibility 
in other developments friday 
police searched the home of robert van tonder leader of the 
rightwing boer state party no one was arrested but police said 
they confiscated documents from the home outside johannesburg 
if they the government carry on this way they can expect 
violence to escalate an angry van tonder said 
police said they arrested three anc guerrillas allegedly 
planning to attack black rivals in the eastern province of natal 
</TEXT>
