was the only state to show a gain in wine consumption last year 
according to a survey 
americans last year drank 211 gallons of wine per capita the 
lowest consumption of any major wineproducing nation and a 58 
percent drop from 1988 according to figures released thursday by 
the trade publication wines amp vines 
by comparison americans over age 21 drank 337 gallons of beer 
216 gallons of distilled spirits and about 35 gallons of coffee 
adultonly wine consumption was 303 gallons per capita 
it was the second straight year wine consumption declined in 
1988 consumption dropped 5 percent from 1987 figures wines amp vines 
mississippi drank the least a mere halfgallon per capita in 
1989 and consumers in the district of columbia the most at 555 
gallons for every man woman and child 
