halfgallon less of wine was consumed last year than in 1988 
domestic table wines still wines not over 14 percent alcohol 
fell 26 percent while production of domestic champagnes dropped 
63 percent last year marked the fourth straight year of decline 
for foreign champagne sales in this country they were down 78 
percent to 12 million gallons 
