and local governments in 198990 added all but about 500 million 
to the 11 billion growth in school revenues over 198889 
according to the report school revenues are reaching the 200 
billion mark the 59 percent increase is the lowest since 1983 and 
leaves virtually no room to meet the costs of school reform and 
restructuring because it nearly matches projected expenditures the 
report showed 
