<TEXT>
the government on friday ordered hawaiibased 
discovery airways closed down in one week accusing the 3monthold 
carrier of violating us laws on foreign ownership 
the transportation department ordered the airline to cancel its 
flights and inform passengers how to obtain refunds or alternate 
transportation 
the department said it agreed with an administrative law judge 
that discoverys officers have consistently provided false 
information and have violated the terms of their temporary 
operating authority and federal law 
transportation secretary samuel skinner announced revocation of 
discoverys temporary operating authority nearly seven months 
before its scheduled expiration 
skinner said the carrier which operates six planes failed to 
show any credible inclination to correct problems with its 
ownership and control 
federal law allows us airlines to have no more than 25 percent 
foreign ownership and requires that they be controlled by us 
citizens 
discovery is 75 percent owned by philip ho president of the 
japanese nansay corps hawaii operations other airlines in the 
area claim that nansay bankrolled hos stake in discovery 
discovery has operated for three months on several interisland 
routes in competition with both hawaiian and aloha airlines those 
carriers claim that discovery is financed by japanese interests and 
run largely by an italian citizen 
in hawaii discovery president don straight said we do not 
agree with their evaluation the decision by the dot appears to 
run directly contrary to airline deregulation he said 
our primary concern is for our customers employees and 
shareholders straight said our objective today will be to see 
if this airline can continue to fly if that is not possible we 
will meet our obligations to our passengers employees and 
vendors 
finally it is our feeling that the real losers in this 
decision are the interisland travelers in the state of hawaii 
straight added airlines are public utilities which provide a 
service to the people this decision by the dot denies the public 
an opportunity to choose and is a disservice to us all 
the administrative law judge ronnie a yoder declared last 
month that cancellation of discoverys permit to operate would 
appear to be a more appropriate action than granting the airline 
a requested extension 
lawyers assigned by the departments public counsel section had 
proposed an arrangement with discovery that would have allowed it 
to operate but yoder recommended against the settlement the judge 
said the carrier had admitted to substantial prior 
misrepresentations when it applied for a permit 
the judge said the fact that the proposed settlement included 
sale of a share in the airline to qualify it as a us carrier was 
an admission that it had operated from its inception as a 
nonus citizen air carrier in violation of the federal aviation 
act and that its submissions to the department were false and 
constituted misrepresentation in violation of federal law 
the department gave discovery until next friday to end its 
service that deadline was set in order to avoid inconvenience to 
travelers spokesman ed ohara said 
if the airline wants to continue to seek a permanent license it 
may proceed with an evidentiary hearing before the law judge the 
spokesman said 
skinner said discovery was given a temporary authority because 
of the departments policy of promoting new entry and competition 
in the airline business 
but he said the airline failed to establish a voting trust that 
would have insulated it from possible foreign control 
the administrative law judge also cited evidence that franco 
mancassola an italian citizen is effectively discoverys 
executive vice president earning twice as much as its president 
hawaiian airlines has filed a 99 million suit against the new 
airline claiming lost revenue because of discoverys allegedly 
fraudulent actions 
</TEXT>
