<TEXT>
a fire at an atomic energy research center 
early saturday caused damage but no injuries officials said 
the fire broke out in the biology laboratory of the democritus 
hellenic atomic energy committee in the northern athens suburb of 
holargos a security official at the building said by telephone 
he said the cause of the fire were not known and that an 
investigation would be held when power was restored to the stricken 
building he spoke on condition of anonymity 
he said that the first two floors of a threefloor building had 
been extensively damaged the building is part of a large walledin 
compound that also houses a small nuclear reactor 
frightened residents telephoned the police when they saw the 
fire at the state institute a spokesman at police headquarters 
said 
he said democritus officials had assured authorities that there 
was no danger of the fire reaching the nuclear reactor housed in 
another building 
the fire was extinguished in two hours said the officer on 
condition of anonymity 
</TEXT>
