<TEXT>
some women are looking over their shoulders 
while walking through midtown manhattan because of a mysterious 
attacker known as the dartman on friday he hit his 52nd victim 
police said 
over the last 10 days the dartman so dubbed by the citys 
tabloid newspapers has repeatedly blown homemade darts at the 
backs and buttocks of welldressed women 
not all of the darts have met their mark some becoming 
entangled in clothing no one has been seriously hurt 
on friday police commissioner lee brown appealed for help from 
the public since the attacker always has struck during daylight in 
the most crowded part of town somebody must have seen him do 
it brown said 
at this time its a nuisance he said adding it doesnt 
make sense we want to put a stop to it 
theres enough to worry about walking through the city without 
this said liz echauss 22 who was dressed in a crisp blue linen 
suit for a job interview 
another woman in a blue business suit was struck at 219 pm 
friday in the latest attack a passerby saw the attack and warned 
the woman who pulled the homemade dart out of her clothing and 
kept walking according to police 
the witness called a police hotline and reported the attack he 
said the man who appeared to have fired the dart fled on foot 
late friday police were trying to determine if a similar attack 
in the borough of queens was related to the manhattan attacks 
a woman in her 40s was walking in the jackson heights section 
around 6 pm when she was struck in her right arm with a 3inch 
dart said sgt nick vreeland she was not seriously hurt 
earlier brown asked people who work in the midtown area to call 
police if they spotted a man resembling the one drawn in a police 
sketch 
police officials have urged women to remain calm despite the 
media attention given the attacks which began june 26th 
for more than a week the dartman who witnesses say is black 
had fired only on white and hispanic women but thursday afternoon 
a 45yearold black woman was struck by a dart while walking to her 
office 
the dartman has struck throughout midtown leaving his mark on 
six women along fifth avenue and more than a dozen along bustling 
seventh avenue between pennsylvania station and times square 
the victims were struck in the buttocks or lower back with the 
2inch homemade darts which were fashioned out of straight pins 
and sewing needles with paper guides and apparently blown through 
straws no foreign substances have been found on any of the darts 
all of the attacks have occurred between 11 am and 7 pm 
illy brown a middleaged software developer looked worried 
when the dartman was mentioned my daughter works in the 
neighborhood my niece works in the neighborhood she said i 
find myself looking suspiciously at anyone on the street who fits 
the description 
debby wehman 23 seemed scared and nervous hes a sick man 
but unfortunately you still have to walk the streets she said 
im trying not to think about it if you walk around thinking 
about it youll make yourself crazy 
