communist north korea today announced 
it will open a short stretch of its border with south korea next 
month to promote reunification a south korean news agency said 
officials in the capitalist south denounced the action as 
propaganda 
if the opening takes place it would be the first time either of 
the two korean states had opened any portion of its border since 
the korean war ended in 1953 
word of the norths move came from naewoe press a semiofficial 
news agency specializing in communist affairs it said north 
koreas committee for the peaceful reunification of the fatherland 
made the surprise announcement in a broadcast monitored in seoul 
today 
