completion and the tanker that caused the nations worst oil spill 
is expected to return to service later this summer 
president gus elmer of exxon shipping co is expected to 
announce today where the tanker will sail and whether it will bear 
the valdez name said exxon spokeswoman janet cool 
cool said the ship would return to service this summer but that 
it was unlikely to sail before august 
the tanker has been undergoing work since august to repair 
damage it sustained on march 24 1989 when it ran aground on a 
reef in alaskas prince william sound the ship spilled almost 11 
million gallons of oil into the sound sullying hundreds of miles 
of coastline and killing scores of wildlife 
