the nations largest teachers union 
abandoned its resistance to allowing engineers scientists and 
other midcareer professionals into the classroom while they study 
to become teachers 
the 2 millionmember national education association had opposed 
socalled alternative certification programs because it said 
recruiting nonteachers to combat faculty shortages undercut 
traditional licensing programs 
