<TEXT>
gold held no luster for us mutual fund 
investors in the second quarter a new survey of mutual fund 
performance says 
goldoriented mutual funds were the lone category to post a 
negative rate of return for the apriljune period according to the 
latest quarterly survey of 1755 mutual funds by lipper analytical 
services inc 
the investment researcher said thursday the best performers were 
mutual funds of health and science stocks and added that funds 
invested in growth stocks generally did better than those invested 
in other stocks or in bonds 
lipper said health and biotechnology funds posted a 1711 
percent return in the second quarter funds invested in science and 
technology stocks had an 1108 percent return the survey said 
it was generally an upbeat quarter for mutual funds which had 
posted a negative rate of return on average in the first three 
months of the year 
the average stock fund including various international and 
speciality stock funds posted a 553 percent rate of return the 
survey said that compared to a negative rate of return of 280 
percent in the first quarter 
but the worst performers were gold funds with a negative return 
of 1027 percent in the quarter all 10 worstperforming funds were 
invested in gold 
a michael lipper president of lipper analytical attributed 
the dull performance to a decline in gold prices a feeling that 
inflation is under control and speculation that the soviet union 
may sell gold while moving toward creation of a marketbased 
economy 
he said the health stock funds appeared to benefit from drug 
introductions and a number of health and biotechnology company 
mergers 
the science and technology funds rose on an improved earnings 
outlook following a prolonged slump lipper said 
lipper said the average general equity fund posted a 589 
percent return in contrast to a negative 231 percent return in the 
first three months of 1990 
lipper said the turnaround occurred in part because of a decline 
in interest rates and the possibility that the opening of markets 
in eastern europe and the soviet union would create new customers 
for us companies 
stock funds invested in companies expected to show earnings 
growth achieved the highest rates of return among the general 
equity funds with 752 percent for small company growth funds and 
703 percent for all types of growth funds 
those performances beat the standard and poors 500 index which 
gained 629 percent in the quarter including estimated dividend 
reinvestment 
capital appreciation funds posted a 586 percernt rate of 
return while growth and income funds had a 473 percernt return 
and equity income funds had a 260 percent return fixed income 
funds had a 318 percent return 
counting funds invested in bonds convertible securities and 
mixtures of bonds and stocks the average longterm taxable fund 
had a rate of return of 465 percent in the quarter compared with 
a negative 195 percent in the first quarter lipper said 
pacific region stock funds had a return of 934 percent 
european region funds a return of 798 percent and international 
funds a 776 percent return 
lippers rankings of 1755 continuing funds for the quarter 
assume investors reinvest all dividends and capital gains 
distributions made by the funds 
the top performing fund was schield progressive environmental 
fund a specialty fund that posted a 2954 percent return 
the denverbased fund has less than 2 million in assets and was 
formed only four months ago in a telephone interview marshall 
schield president of schield management said the fund invests in 
sociallyresponsible companies whose business is cleaning up the 
environment 
that fund was followed by fidelity select biotechnology a 
health stock fund at 2357 percent and bull amp bear select 
equities which invests in stocks for capital appreciation at 
2238 percent 
the worst performer was strategic investments a gold fund with 
a negative return of 2355 percent next were us gold shares with 
a a negative return of 1653 percent and us new prospector fund 
another gold fund with a negative return of 1496 percent 
