<TEXT>
air france was forced to cancel more than 60 
flights friday because of a strike by ground personnel at charles 
de gaulle airport outside paris 
the strike for higher wages and better working conditions by 
hundreds of baggage handlers hostesses and agents began a day 
after the end of a disruptive threeday strike by parisarea air 
traffic controllers 
air france which initially said the new strike would cause only 
minor disruptions admitted its problems turned out to be severe 
it cancelled about half its flights in and out of charles de 
gaulle including about 50 mediumrange flights and a dozen 
longrange flights 
the strike is scheduled to end at midday saturday and the 
stateowned airline said it expected to be able to operate all of 
its longrange flights that day except one from paris to dakar 
senegal it cancelled 14 mediumrange flights saturday 
most of the flights cancelled friday were to european cities 
including london frankfurt amsterdam and geneva which air france 
serves with numerous flights each day it maintained service to 
these cities on a reduced basis 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

