<TEXT>
page group publishing inc has 
purchased a pair of readerwritten magazines in beverly hills and 
brentwood 
page group headed by former chicago suntimes publisher robert 
e page bought the glendale news press and the costa mesabased 
orange coast daily pilot last year 
page said thursday he paid between 1 million and 2 million for 
the brentwood blabla and beverly hills the magazine which are 
distributed free 
the beverly hills publication has a circulation of 65000 the 
west los angeles magazine 75000 according to their founder and 
former majority owner michael lobkowicz 
the magazines feature prose artwork poetry and reviews 
submitted by readers published virtually unedited no payment is 
given to the authors who have included such wellknown local 
residents as zsa zsa gabor kenny rogers and norman lear 
page said he hoped to build a regional media company when he led 
an investor group that purchased the glendale and costa mesa papers 
last year 
he purchased the magazines from metropolitan media inc in west 
los angeles lobkowicz will stay on as their publisher and there 
are no plans to change the editorial content or the staff of 26 
people page said 
the costa mesabased page group also owns weekly newspapers in 
huntington beach burbank and la canada flintridge 
lobkowicz said a third magazine that he launched recently 
titled the prince and the bear will be reformulated to appear as a 
readerwritten insert in thursday editions of the daily pilot 
</TEXT>
