<TEXT>
oil prices wound up a slow week with mostly 
minor changes friday as crude kept to a tight trading range 
volume was extremely light because many market participants took 
an extended break after the independence day holiday on wednesday 
reports of renewed output disruptions due to an illegal strike 
by norwegian oil workers initially inspired crude buying in the 
energy futures pits on the new york mercantile exchange 
but the rally fizzled after it became apparent that the bulk of 
norways oil production was resuming 
wholesale gasoline prices firmed on speculation that an 
explosion and fire at an arco chemical co plant in texas could 
cause a temporary shortage in a gas additive the plant makes an 
additive used to upgrade gas to premium 
the contract for august delivery of west texas intermediate 
dipped 3 cents to 1647 per 42gallon barrel after slumping 30 
cents thursday contracts for delivery during september through 
november also posted modest losses 
unleaded gasoline for august delivery rose 046 cent to 5541 
cents a gallon after sliding 114 cents thursday the contracts for 
delivery through november also settled higher 
among other refined products traded on the exchange wholesale 
home heating oil for august delivery settled at 4830 cents a 
gallon off 003 cent the contract ended down 013 cent on 
thursday the september through november contracts finished mixed 
in natural gas trading the august contract fell to 1498 per 
1000 cubic feet from 1514 thursday 
energy broker andrew lebow at edampf man international futures 
inc said no clear price patterns emerged friday or the entire 
week because activity was so sluggish 
he said the arco chemical plant fire in channelview texas 
tended to encourage buying of premium gas on the gulf coast 
</TEXT>
