<TEXT>
the texas water commission recommended a 
2cent per barrel fee on crude oil moving through ports on the 
states gulf coast 
the money would help pay for cleanups of future oil spills 
the fee would be charged until the balance in the texas spill 
response fund is raised from 750000 to 50 million the levy 
would be applied as needed to maintain that balance the commission 
said 
approximately 560 million barrels of crude oil pass through 
oilloading facilities by tanker along the texas gulf coast every 
year the commission said it said the fee would raise more than 
11 million per year 
since several oil and chemical companies have large plants in 
both texas and louisiana the commission also said the new funding 
mechanism should be coordinated with louisiana otherwise shippers 
might go to louisiana to avoid the fee 
interest and principal of the fund would be used to finance 
standby oil spill response contracts and stateowned equipment 
stockpiles 
the money also could pay for a research and development program 
for new oil spill technology such as the bioremediation used in 
the mega borg spill 
in that process bacteria was used to eat the oil and turn it 
into a fatty acid that could be consumed by marine life 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> AP900706-0258 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
two measures of the nations money supply rose 
in late june while a broader money measure fell the federal 
reserve board reported friday 
in a report delayed by one day due to the independence day 
holiday the fed said the narrowest measure of the money supply 
m1 rose 13 billion to a seasonally adjusted 8088 billion in 
the week ended june 25 from a revised 8075 billion in the 
previous week 
the central bank said a measure known as m2 advanced 1 billion 
to a seasonally adjusted 32705 billion from 32695 billion the 
previous week 
but an even broader measure m3 dropped 41 billion to a 
seasonally adjusted 40539 billion from 40580 billion 
m1 includes cash in circulation deposits in checking accounts 
and nonbank travelers checks m2 is m1 plus accounts like savings 
deposits and moneymarket mutual funds m3 is m2 plus lessliquid 
accounts such as certificates of deposit in minimum denominations 
of 100000 
in judging its monetary policy the fed has indicated it is 
monitoring the value of the dollar commodity prices and the 
difference between short and longterm interest rates it also has 
shifted its attention from m1 to the two broader money supply 
measures 
the annual growth rate in m2 so far this year is 44 percent 
which is within the feds target range of 3 percent to 7 percent 
the annual growth rate in m3 was 17 percent which is below the 
feds target range of 25 percent to 65 percent the fed has not 
set a target for m1 growth since early 1987 
for the latest 13 weeks m2 averaged 32673 billion a 34 
percent seasonally adjusted annual rate of gain from the previous 
13 weeks m3 averaged 40605 billion up 05 percent while m1 
rose 34 percent to an average of 8068 billion 
in other reports 
the federal reserve bank of new york reported commercial and 
industrial loans at major banks fell 13 billion in the week ended 
june 27 compared with a gain of 101 billion a week earlier 
the federal reserve said bank borrowings from the federal 
reserve system at the discount window excluding extended credit 
